Governor Ibrahim Hassan Dankwambo of Gombe State has declared Monday (today) as work free day across the state to mourn the death of a former governor of the state, late Abubakar Habu Hashidu. Daily Trust had reported that the late Hashidu aged 74, died last Friday in his private residence in Gombe after a protracted illness. His remains were buried on Friday at the Gombe Central Cemetery after a funeral prayer at the Gombe emir's palace. A press statement signed by the Acting Secretary to the State Government, Mr James Pisaghi, said workers are also expected to offer special prayers for the repose of the deceased soul. According to the statement, the workers would resume work at their respective offices on Tuesday. Mr Pisaghi said late Habu Hashidu has contributed immensely during the struggle for the creation of the state, having served as secretary of the movement. Late Hashidu was the first civilian governor of the state, he was in office from May 29, 1999 to May 29, 2003. He was survived by one wife and eight children.